The paper discusses worst-case optimal join algorithms in the context of databases, which suggests that it belongs to the cs.DB (database) sub-category. The paper also proposes a new data structure for representing relations as point sets in variable-dimensional grids, which suggests that it belongs to the cs.DS (data structures and algorithms) sub-category. The paper further discusses the running time of the proposed algorithm, which suggests that it belongs to the cs.DC (distributed, parallel, and cluster computing) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of a compositional algorithm, which suggests that it belongs to the cs.CC (computational complexity) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the extension of the framework to compute more expressive queries in relational algebra, which suggests that it belongs to the cs.LG (machine learning) sub-category.
